  "prompt": "Are there legal frameworks in place to combat money laundering?",
  "response": "Yes, there are several legal frameworks in place to combat money laundering at national and international levels:\n\n1. International frameworks:\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- United Nations Convention against Transnational Organized Crime\n- Egmont Group of Financial Intelligence Units\n\n2. National legislation:\n- Bank Secrecy Act (United States)\n- Proceeds of Crime Act (United Kingdom)\n- Anti-Money Laundering/Countering Financing of Terrorism (AML/CFT) regulations\n\n3. Key regulatory requirements:\n- Customer due diligence\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) procedures\n- Suspicious transaction reporting\n- Record-keeping requirements\n- Enhanced monitoring of high-risk transactions\n\n4. Enforcement mechanisms:\n- Financial investigations\n- Asset seizure\n- Criminal prosecution\n- Significant financial penalties\n- International cooperation between law enforcement agencies\n\n5. Emerging technologies:\n- Advanced digital monitoring systems\n- Blockchain and AI-based transaction tracking\n- Enhanced data analytics for detecting suspicious activities\n\nThese frameworks aim to prevent criminals from disguising illegally obtained funds and integrating them into legitimate financial systems.",
